âœ… SECTION 1 â€” Executive Summary

1.1 Overview

The Royal Ambassadors of Nigeria Portal (Ogun Baptist Conference) is a digital platform designed to manage and streamline the operations of the Royal Ambassadors organization. It supports:

Ambassador management

Administrative supervision by Association Presidents

Complete oversight by the Super Admin

Exam systems

Camp registrations

Payments

Blogs

Gallery

Notifications

Rank promotion

Result tracking


The existing system is a PHP monolithic structure with frontend HTML/CSS/JS embedded directly in .php templates.

This PRD establishes the requirements and specifications for rebuilding the entire frontend in React + TypeScript, while retaining a clean PHP API backend.


---

1.2 Problem Statement

The current monolithic PHP application presents several challenges:

UI is not modern or scalable

Frontend and backend tightly coupled

Hard to maintain and extend

Limited interactivity

No component reusability

No API-driven architecture

Styling inconsistencies

Organization cannot grow the platform efficiently



---

1.3 Proposed Solution

A complete decoupling:

Frontend â†’ React + TypeScript + Vite + Tailwind
Backend â†’ PHP (REST API) + MySQL

This structure enables:

Modern UI/UX

Faster user interaction

Easier maintenance

API-based architecture

Better role-based experience

Reusable components

Scalability for future features

Integration with mobile apps (future phase)



---

1.4 Target Users

1. Ambassadors (Users)


2. Association Presidents (Admins)


3. Super Admin (Conference-wide control)


4. Future system: Central Baptist authority




---

1.5 PRD Purpose

This PRD defines:

Functional requirements

Non-functional requirements

Backend API expectations

UI/UX rules

Theming guidelines

Component hierarchy

Role permissions

Navigation structure

Data workflows

Background animation rules

Future planning


This PRD will act as the source of truth for:

Antigravity (React refactor)

Backend API restructuring

QA testing

Documentation

Long-term roadmap



