ğŸš€ SECTION 3 â€” User Roles & Permissions

This section includes:

1. Full role descriptions


2. Responsibilities


3. Restrictions


4. Permission matrix




---

3.1 Role Descriptions

1. Ambassador (User)

This is the primary user class representing boys in the Royal Ambassadors program.

Capabilities:

Sign up

Log in

View dashboard

Take exams (when approved)

Upload payment receipts

View exam results

View notifications

Register for camps

View blog

View gallery

Update profile


Restrictions:

Cannot approve themselves for exams

Cannot view admin/super admin pages

Cannot manage content

Cannot access finance tools



---

2. Association President (Admin)

Represents administrators for each RA association.

Capabilities:

Log in with special passcode

Manage ambassadors in their association

Approve ambassadors for exams

Upload Excel sheets for camp registration

Upload payment receipts (dues, exams, camps)

View all payments in their association

View statistics for their association

View and send notifications


Restrictions:

Cannot see data from other associations

Cannot create global exams

Cannot approve payments

Cannot manage blog/gallery



---

3. Super Admin

The highest-level authority with full control.

Capabilities:

Log in with super admin passcode

Manage all users (ambassadors + admins)

Create/modify/delete exams

Add questions

Approve exam scores

Track all payments

Approve/reject payments

Issue PDF receipts

Manage associations

Manage the entire gallery

Manage the entire blog

View all camp registrations

Assign or remove presidents

Send global notifications


Restrictions:
None â€” full access.


---

