ğŸ“˜ SECTION 11 â€” Non-Functional Requirements (NFRs)

Performance

Pages must load in under 1.5 seconds

React components must be lazy-loaded

Images must be optimized


Security

JWT authentication

Rate limiting API endpoints

Password hashing: PASSWORD_BCRYPT

Role-based route protection


Scalability

Stateless React frontend

Modularized components

PHP API enables future mobile apps


Consistency

Colors only from Tailwind theme tokens

Components never inline-style

UI never modified unless PRD says so



---

ğŸ“˜ SECTION 12 â€” Antigravity Reinforcement Rules

These rules prevent redesign or inconsistencies.

1. UI must look EXACTLY like the current PHP version

Same structure.
Same spacing.
Same alignment.
Same layouts.

2. Only code changes â€” not design changes.

3. React + TypeScript must use the folder structure in this PRD.

4. Tailwind must use navy-gold theme tokens from theme.ts.

5. All animations must follow A + D rules exactly.

6. No new components unless PRD specifies.

7. Backend API endpoints must follow definitions in Section 5.

8. No mixing backend logic into frontend components.

9. All feature behavior must match legacy PHP system 1:1.


---

